gobblin.data.management.conversion.hive.watermarker

Class PartitionLevelWatermarker

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.data.management.conversion.hive.watermarker.PartitionLevelWatermarker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HiveSourceWatermarker

    public class PartitionLevelWatermarker
extends Object
implements HiveSourceWatermarker
    A HiveSourceWatermarker that maintains watermarks for each Partition. For every Table it creates a NoOp WorkUnit that stores watermarks for all its Partitions. The Noop workunit is identified by the property IS_WATERMARK_WORKUNIT_KEY being set to true.

    The watermark used is the update time of a Partition (for partitioned tables) or update time of a Table (for non partitioned tables).

    The watermark is stored as a MultiKeyValueLongWatermark which is an extension to Map that implements gobblin's Watermark. The key is a Partition identifier and value is the watermark for this Partition

    Watermarks for all Partitions modified after HiveSource.HIVE_SOURCE_MAXIMUM_LOOKBACK_DAYS_KEY are retained. The default is HiveSource.DEFAULT_HIVE_SOURCE_MAXIMUM_LOOKBACK_DAYS. If a previous watermark is not found for as partition, it returns 0 as the watermark

    Watermark workunits are not created for non partitioned tables

      • onGetWorkunitsEnd

        public void onGetWorkunitsEnd(List<WorkUnit> workunits)
        Adds watermark workunits to workunits. A watermark workunit is a dummy workunit that is skipped by extractor/converter/writer. It stores a map of watermarks. The map has one entry per partition with partition watermark as value.
        • Add one NoOp watermark workunit for each Table
        • The workunit has an identifier property IS_WATERMARK_WORKUNIT_KEY set to true.
        • Watermarks for all Partitions that belong to this Table are added as Map
        • A maximum of #maxPartitionsPerDataset are persisted. Watermarks are ordered by most recently modified Partitions
        A callback method executed before a list of workunits is returned by the HiveSource.getWorkunits(gobblin.configuration.SourceState) to the caller
        Specified by:
        onGetWorkunitsEnd in interface HiveSourceWatermarker
        Parameters:
        workunits - constructed by HiveSource.getWorkunits(gobblin.configuration.SourceState)
        See Also:
        HiveSourceWatermarker.onGetWorkunitsEnd(java.util.List)
